This huge range of severity of Covid-19 cases is part of what makes it such a horrific health crisis.
Among the top questions: What leads one person with the virus to severe disease, and another to have no or few symptoms?
The “infection enigma”While the most severe Covid-19 cases are concerning, it’s actually not unusual to have a big range.
The biological pathways that lead to severe disease for one virus might not be the same pathways that lead to severe disease with another virus.
Unfortunately, in not knowing who is most vulnerable to get severe Covid-19, we may have to assume anyone can be.